{
  "design_notes": "S0 acts as a very minimal introduction, introducing the three lanes with only two spaced-out notes to give players time to settle. S1 thins out considerably with a highly structured, slow-paced beat-matching sequence, leaving 2-beat gaps on odd bars to ensure the break section breathes heavily. S2 escalates the energy smoothly, scaling up from 1.0-beat steps to a dense, continuous synth cascade of alternating 0.5-beat sweeps right at its peak (beats 52 to 60.5). S3 winds down gently, concluding with a symmetric three-lane walk-down to resolve the chart cleanly.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "S0",
      "start_bar": 0,
      "intent": "Minimal introduction to familiarize the player with the three lanes."
    },
    {
      "name": "S1",
      "start_bar": 1,
      "intent": "Relaxed rhythm play to allow the break to breathe cleanly with 2-beat gaps."
    },
    {
      "name": "S2",
      "start_bar": 7,
      "intent": "The main drop, building density towards an intense but casual-friendly 0.5-beat alternation climax."
    },
    {
      "name": "S3",
      "start_bar": 15,
      "intent": "A satisfying outro walk-down to resolve the chart as the music fades."
    }
  ],
